      • checkExpirationData

        public static boolean checkExpirationData(java.lang.String expiryDateString)
        Checks the card expiration data
        Parameters:
        expiryDateString - Takes in a String formatted like any of these (Note the leading Zero): 0219 <-- Feb, 2019 0412 <-- April, 2012 122020 <-- December, 2020 0121 <-- January, 2021
        Returns:
        Boolean, true if data is good, false if it is bad

      • checkCreditCardNumber

        public static <T extends android.widget.ImageView> boolean checkCreditCardNumber(CreditCardUtilities.CardType typeCard,
                                                                                 T imageToSet,
                                                                                 int visibilityTypeIfWrongCard,
                                                                                 int visibilityTypeIfRightCard,
                                                                                 CreditCardUtilities.CardType onlyTypeTrue)
        This method checks the validity of a credit card via typeCard
        Type Parameters:
        T - T extends ImageView
        Parameters:
        typeCard - Type of card being passed in of type CreditCardUtilities.CardType
        imageToSet - ImageView to set the credit card logo image into
        visibilityTypeIfWrongCard - The visibility type to set if the wrong card (IE Visibility.GONE)
        visibilityTypeIfRightCard - The visibility type to set if the right card (IE Visibility.VISIBLE)
        onlyTypeTrue - Object of type CreditCardUtilities.CardType. Will only return true if the decided card is of this type. This would be used if you only want to allow 1 specific card type (IE Visa only)
        Returns:
        Boolean, true if the card is a valid one and matches passed type

      • checkCreditCardNumber

        public static <T extends android.widget.ImageView> boolean checkCreditCardNumber(CreditCardUtilities.CardType typeCard,
                                                                                 T imageToSet,
                                                                                 int visibilityTypeIfWrongCard,
                                                                                 int visibilityTypeIfRightCard,
                                                                                 CreditCardUtilities.CardType[] onlyTypeTrue)
        This method checks the validity of a credit card via typeCard
        Type Parameters:
        T - T extends ImageView
        Parameters:
        typeCard - Type of card being passed in of type CreditCardUtilities.CardType
        imageToSet - ImageView to set the credit card logo image into
        visibilityTypeIfWrongCard - The visibility type to set if the wrong card (IE Visibility.GONE)
        visibilityTypeIfRightCard - The visibility type to set if the right card (IE Visibility.VISIBLE)
        onlyTypeTrue - Array of type CreditCardUtilities.CardType. Will only return true if the decided card is of one of these types. This would be used if you only want to allow specific card types (IE Visa && AMEX && Mastercard)
        Returns:
        Boolean, true if the card is a valid one and matches passed type
